1.title: Bad Trip
1.plot: In Oscar's never ending search for water, he comes across a nice cold bottle, but how to open it...

2.title: Egg Race
2.plot: Buck, Popy and Harchi try to use Oscar and a fishing pole to catch chickens. Harchi uses a View-Master instead of real binoculars like Popy and Buck. This is the first time that Oscar makes the "Scared-of-the-chickens" face.

3.title: Finding Water
3.plot: Oscar makes various attempts to locate water which Buck, Popy and Harchi attempt to steal.

4.title: Baby Doll
4.plot: Oscar realizes that he is alone while the other desert creatures have family and friends.

5.title: Falling in Love
5.plot: Oscar meets a potential mate who is promptly abducted by a hungry chicken.

6.title: The Fly
6.plot: Oscar attempts to devour a juicy looking but very resourceful big green fly. Buck, Popy and Harchi try skitching.

7.title: Hot Dog Way of Life
7.plot: The desert is hotter and more dry than usual. Chaos ensues while trying to find relief.

8.title: Walking on the Moon
8.plot: Oscar thinks that the Moon would make the perfect evening snack.

9.title: Chicken Charmer
9.plot: While trying to make beautiful music, Oscar discovers a way to hypnotize chickens.

10.title: Oasis Cup
10.plot: Oscar mistakes a ball for an egg as Popy and Harchi play extreme tennis.

11.title: Home Sweet Home
11.plot: Oscar is inspired to build a home. Buck, Popy and Harchi have a loud party at night.

imdb.title: Oscar's Oasis
plot: Follows the sun-baked adventures of Oscar, a lizard in the middle of the desert finding himself misadventures wherever he goes, from finding water to fleeing from a band of misfits.::Anonymous
synopsis:
Lost, smack in the middle of an arid desert, all of them are trying to survive and above all to not die
from boredom. The conditions for survival are therefore, in priority order: find water, find shade, find
something to eat, find something to do.The stories start with the main character, Oscar. He always has a precise objective and he deploys all of his ingenuity, imagination, energy and optimism to reach his goal: find something to drink, to eat, to understand the mechanism of an object found in the sand, avoid the beaks of the chickens who like to peck at lizard loin chops...
Each time, the trio of turbulent friends crosses Oscars route. And each time the young, energetic reptiles
objectives tend to get seriously compromised. Its nothing personal. The trio dont want to catch Oscar. Sometimes, its just that theyre after the same thing. Oscar doesnt hold it against them, hes not the type to hold a grudge
